Meristem Securities Limited, a foremost financial service provider, has unveiled a new TV Commercial – Grow. Preserve. Transfer, aimed at ramping up activities to grow and preserve investors’ wealth. The organisation said it has been growing wealth, preserving it during stormy times, and assisting in transferring it on to the next generation. “Building wealth isn’t only what you do for yourself, it’s what you do for generations to come,” it said. According to the firm, that line in the new TV commercial aptly captures the company’s promise of Growth, Preservation and Transfer. The new commercial features Allyson-Aina Davies, daughter of famous Art Gallery Owner, Nike Okundaye in her Art studio who is following right in the footsteps of her mother. The choice of Aina signifies the importance of not just growing wealth but preserving and transferring it through the right investment choices. GMD, Meristem Securities Limited, Wole Abegunde, said the firm remains committed to grow people’s wealth and preserve it for future generations.